race.comment: RUSSIAN FRONT (2) is going much better than form suggests. Coming back in journey and back in grade. Drawn for a soft run and should be picking up strongly and running on hard. PREVENTION (11) was fair on rain affected ground on debut then improved sharply at second outing to score the maiden win. Drawn to track the speed again and expected to measure up. STOLEN ART (3) was a winner two back then not far from the winner last time. Ideally drawn here and gets chance to atone.  KING'S TAJ (6) settled back but cruised up out wide and ran on to score a comfortable win last time. At peak and drawn for a good run here. Looks one of the main hopes again.
